# this is a function from Kayla, for splitting taxa names 
    name.split<-function(names){
      names=names
      save=strsplit(names,"/") # strsplit() is a function like seperate(vector, "the-seperate-mark")
                                # names in the names-vector is the first level
                                  # save is the second level, so we need to use save[[]] to call 
      h=0
      for(i in 1:length(names)){ # for loop for each name
        h[i]=length(save[[i]])} # h is an indicator of each level of taxa name
      
      i=0
      name.list=NULL
      for(i in 1:length(save)){ # for loop to get each level of the taxa 
        name.list[i]=save[[i]][h[i]]}
      return(name.list)
    }

    rblock<- function(nb) { # to create a block diagonal matrix
      .bdiag(replicate(nb, {
        Matrix(c(0,1,1,0), 2,2) }))
    }
DigestCounts <- Digest_counts %>% # the digets counts now is a tibble form
  remove_rownames %>% # set the OTU_Names as the rownames
  column_to_rownames(var="OTU_Name") # colunm_to_rownames and rownames_to_column is very easy to use

DigestCounts["root", ] <- DigestCounts["root", ]-DigestCounts["Unclassified", ]-DigestCounts["Bacteria", ] # adjust root
DigestRel <- DigestCounts %>% 
  rownames_to_column("OTU_Name") %>% # set the rownames as OTU_Names
  filter(OTU_Name!="Unclassified")  %>% # delect the Unclassified
  filter(OTU_Name!="Bacteria") %>% # delect the Bacteria
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") %>%
  t() %>% # set the ID as the columnnames, but tidyverse does not have this function, 
          # so we have to tranform the matrix, in order to use column_to_rownames
  as.data.frame() %>% # after transpose, the dataset is a matrix, so need to set up as data.frame again
  rownames_to_column("ID") %>%
  mutate_at(vars(-ID, -root), funs(. / root)) %>% # calculate the ratio except the Total
  column_to_rownames("ID") %>% 
  select(-root) %>%
  t() %>% # now transpose the data.frame back
  as.data.frame() %>% # do not forget set the matrix to data.frame again
  rownames_to_column("OTU_Name") # now the column name is the ID,

DigestAlpha <- Digest_alpha %>% 
  arrange(Collection) %>% # arrange the order alphabetically
  separate(Collection, into=c("Method","ID"), sep=1) %>% # set up the Method and ID
  separate(ID, into=c("ID","EnzD"), sep=4) %>% # set up the digestion method
  mutate(EnzD=replace(EnzD, EnzD!="D", "N")) %>% # add variable for digestion
  mutate(Peilous=`ShannonH Median`/log(`Sobs Median`)) %>% # add variable for Peilous
  select(ID, Method, EnzD, `Sobs Median`, 
        `ShannonH Median`, Peilous, everything()) # just reorder the columns, 
                                                  # otherwise the new variables will be add to the last
OPAlpha <- DigestAlpha %>% # filter out all the OP
  filter(Method=="C")

SPAlpha <- DigestAlpha %>% # filter out all the SP
  filter(Method=="E")

DigestRel_OP <- DigestRel %>%
  select("OTU_Name", contains("C")) %>% # select all the samples with "C" or OP
  select("OTU_Name", noquote(order(colnames(.)))) %>%
  filter(`OTU_Name` != "root")

DigestRel_OP_Med_row <- DigestRel_OP %>% # to find the median of each OTU_name
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") %>%
  as.matrix() %>%
  rowMedians() %>% # rowMedians to calculate the Median for each row
                    # to get the columnMedians just transpose the data.frame
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(Median=".") %>% # can also used the mutate() function
  cbind(DigestRel_OP) %>% # if use mutate(), do not need to cbind with orginial data anymore
  select(OTU_Name, Median, everything()) # reorder

DigestRel_OP_Names <- DigestRel_OP_Med_row %>%
  filter(`Median`>=0.01) %>% # only get teh Median>=0.01 names
  select(OTU_Name) %>% 
  remove_rownames() %>% # now the data is one column data.frame
  unlist() %>% 
  as.character()

DigestCounts_OP <- DigestCounts %>%
  rownames_to_column(var=("OTU_Name")) %>%
  filter( OTU_Name %in% DigestRel_OP_Names) %>%
  select("OTU_Name", contains("C")) %>% # select all the samples with "C" or OP
  select("OTU_Name", noquote(order(colnames(.)))) %>% # to reorder 
  mutate(Species=name.split(OTU_Name)) %>% # use the function to split the taxa names
  select(Species, everything()) %>%
  select(-OTU_Name) %>%
  column_to_rownames(var="Species") %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame()
PCoA_OP <- DigestCounts_OP %>%
  vegdist(method="morisita") %>% # need more reading to learn this function
  cmdscale() %>% # morisita 
  as.data.frame() %>%
  select(Dim1=`V1`, Dim2=`V2`)

Species_OP <- envfit(PCoA_OP, DigestCounts_OP)
Species_OP_df<-as.data.frame(cbind(Species_OP$vectors$arrows*sqrt(Species_OP$vectors$r),Species_OP$vectors$pvals))
Species_OP_df$Species<-rownames(Species_OP_df)
colnames(Species_OP_df)<-c("Dim1","Dim2","Pvals","Species")
# Species_OP_df<-Species_OP_df[Species_OP_df$Pvals<.005,]

DataSet_OP <- cbind(PCoA_OP, DigestCounts_OP) %>%
  rownames_to_column(var="Collection") %>%
  separate(Collection, into=c("Method","ID"), sep=1) %>% # set up the Method and ID
  separate(ID, into=c("ID","EnzD"), sep=4) %>% # set up the digestion method
  mutate(EnzD=replace(EnzD, EnzD!="D", "N")) # add variable for digestion

Plot_OP <- ggplot(DataSet_OP,aes(x=Dim1,y=Dim2,group=ID, color=EnzD)) +
  geom_line(col="black",linetype="dotted") +
  geom_point(size=3) +
  guides( col=F, size=F) +
  geom_segment(data=Species_OP_df,
               aes(x=0,xend=Dim1,y=0,yend=Dim2), 
               arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.5, "cm")), 
               colour="black", stat="identity",
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +
  geom_text(data=Species_OP_df,
            aes(x=Dim1,y=Dim2,label=Species),
            inherit.aes = FALSE, size=5) +
  coord_fixed() +
  xlim(-1,1) +
  ylim(-1,1) +
  theme_bw() +
  ggthemes::scale_colour_wsj("colors6") +
  ggtitle("Ordination Biplot", "Beta diveristy values for OP swabs") +
  labs(y="Component2", x="Component1") +
  theme(text = element_text(size=15))
Plot_OP

DataSet_SP1 <- DataSet_SP %>%
  filter(Dim1 <= -0.1 & Dim2 >= -0.25) %>%
  mutate(Cluster="C1") %>%
  select(ID, EnzD, Dim1, Dim2, Cluster)
DataSet_SP2 <- DataSet_SP %>%
  filter(Dim2 <= -0.3) %>%
  mutate(Cluster="C2") %>%
  select(ID, EnzD, Dim1, Dim2, Cluster)
DataSet_SP3 <- DataSet_SP %>%
  filter(Dim1 > -0.1 & Dim2 > -0.3) %>%
  mutate(Cluster="C3") %>%
  select(ID, EnzD, Dim1, Dim2, Cluster)
DataSet_SPAll <- rbind(DataSet_SP1, DataSet_SP2, DataSet_SP3) %>%
  as.data.frame()

Diversity <- DigestRel %>%
  select(-Total) %>%
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  cbind(., DivIndex=diversity(., index="shannon")) %>%
  rownames_to_column(var="Collection") %>%
  separate(Collection, into=c("Method","ID"), sep=1) %>% # set up the Method and ID
  separate(ID, into=c("ID","EnzD"), sep=4) %>% # set up the digestion method
  mutate(EnzD=replace(EnzD, EnzD!="D", "N")) %>%  # add variable for digestion
  select(Method, ID, EnzD, DivIndex)
Diversity_SP <- inner_join(DataSet_SPAll, Diversity, by=c("ID"="ID", "EnzD"="EnzD"))
Plot_Diversity <- Diversity_SP %>%
  ggplot(aes(Cluster, DivIndex, col=Cluster)) +
  geom_boxplot(show.legend = F) +
  facet_grid(~EnzD) +
  ggthemes::scale_colour_wsj("colors6") +
  theme_bw() +
  ggtitle("Ordination Biplot", "Beta diveristy values for Sputum") +
  labs(y="Alpha Diversity Index", x="Clusters") +
  theme(text = element_text(size=15))
Plot_Diversity

kruskal.test(data=Diversity_SP, DivIndex~Cluster)

AbsoluteRel_OP_D <- DigestRel_OP %>%
  filter( OTU_Name %in% DigestRel_OP_Names) %>%
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("Collection") %>%
  separate(Collection, into=c("Method","ID"), sep=1) %>% # set up the Method and ID
  separate(ID, into=c("ID","EnzD"), sep=4) %>% # set up the digestion method
  mutate(EnzD=replace(EnzD, EnzD!="D", "N")) %>%
  filter(EnzD=="D") %>%
  select(-Method, -EnzD) %>%
  column_to_rownames("ID")

AbsoluteRel_OP_N <- DigestRel_OP %>%
  filter( OTU_Name %in% DigestRel_OP_Names) %>%
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("Collection") %>%
  separate(Collection, into=c("Method","ID"), sep=1) %>% # set up the Method and ID
  separate(ID, into=c("ID","EnzD"), sep=4) %>% # set up the digestion method
  mutate(EnzD=replace(EnzD, EnzD!="D", "N")) %>%
  filter(EnzD=="N") %>%
  select(-Method, -EnzD) %>%
  column_to_rownames("ID")

wilcoxon_pair_row <- function(x, y){wilcox.exact(x, y, paired=T, conf.int=T)}
Wilcoxon_OP1 <- map2(AbsoluteRel_OP_D, AbsoluteRel_OP_N, .f=wilcoxon_pair_row)
# Wilcoxon_OP2 <- map2(AbsoluteRel_OP_D, AbsoluteRel_OP_N, .f=row_wilcoxon_paired)
# # asecond method to check the p-values.

Wilcoxon_OP_est <- Wilcoxon_OP1 %>% # ?????? why "map(return(.$estimate))" does not work??????
  map(function(x) return(x$estimate)) %>%
  unlist() %>%
  round(4) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  transmute(`Estimate Change in RA %`=.*100)

Wilcoxon_OP_pval <- Wilcoxon_OP1 %>% 
  map(function(x) return(x$p.value)) %>%
  unlist() %>%
  p.adjust(method="BH") %>%
  round(2) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(`p-value`=".") %>%
  ifelse(.$`p-value`<=0.01, "<0.01", .) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(`p-value`=".")

AbsoluteRel_OP_D_Median <- AbsoluteRel_OP_D %>%
  t() %>%
  as.matrix() %>%
  rowMedians() %>%
  round(4) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  transmute(`EnzD %`=.*100) 

AbsoluteRel_OP_N_Median <- AbsoluteRel_OP_N %>%
  t() %>%
  as.matrix() %>%
  rowMedians() %>%
  round(4) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  transmute(`NonD %`=.*100)

Table_OP <- names(AbsoluteRel_OP_D) %>%
  name.split() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(Genera=".") %>%
  cbind.data.frame(AbsoluteRel_OP_D_Median, AbsoluteRel_OP_N_Median, Wilcoxon_OP_est, Wilcoxon_OP_pval) %>% 
  column_to_rownames("Genera") %>%
  xtable()
View(Table_OP)
print(Table_OP)

  hold <- wilcox.exact(SP_Vals[,i+3]~SP_Vals$EnzD, paired=T)
  SP_bps_p[i] <- hold$p.value
}

  round(2) %>%

  ifelse(.==0.01, paste("p<", ., sep=""),.) %>%
  ifelse(.!="p<0.01", paste("p=", ., sep=""),.) %>%
  ifelse(nchar(.)==5, paste(., "0", sep=""), .)

  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("Phyla") %>%
  filter(Phyla %in% unlist(rownames(Phyla_SP_N_Median))) %>%
  column_to_rownames("Phyla")

Phyla_SP_N_abs <- Phyla_SP_N_Rel %>%
  as.matrix() %>%
  rowMedians() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  select(Median=1) %>%
  transmute(`Nondigested %`=Median*100) %>%
  cbind(rownames(Phyla_SP_N_Median)) %>%
  column_to_rownames("rownames(Phyla_SP_N_Median)")

Phyla__SP_estimate <- map(Phyla_SP_wilcoxon, function(x) return(x$estimate)) %>%
  unlist() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(Estimates=1) %>%
  transmute(`Estimate in RA %` = Estimates*100) %>%
  round(4) %>%
  cbind(rownames(Phyla_SP_N_Median)) %>%
  column_to_rownames("rownames(Phyla_SP_N_Median)")
View(Phyla__SP_estimate)

Phyla_SP_pval <- map(Phyla_SP_wilcoxon, function(x) return(x$p.value)) %>%
  unlist() %>%
  p.adjust(method="BH") %>%
  round(4) %>%
  ifelse(.<=0.01, "<0.01", .) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(`p-value`=1)

Phyla_SP_table <- cbind(Phyla_SP_D_abs, Phyla_SP_N_abs, Phyla__SP_estimate, Phyla_SP_pval) %>%
  rownames_to_column("Phyla name")

DigestRel_D <- DigestRel %>%
  select("OTU_Name", contains("D")) %>% 
  select("OTU_Name", noquote(order(colnames(.)))) %>%
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") 

DigestRel_N <- DigestRel %>%
  select(-contains("D")) %>% 
  select("OTU_Name", noquote(order(colnames(.)))) %>%
  column_to_rownames("OTU_Name") 

Odiv_D <- DigestRel_D %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  diversity(index="shannon") %>%
  as.data.frame()
View(Odiv_D)
Odiv_N <- DigestRel_N %>%
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  diversity(index="shannon") %>%
  as.data.frame()

Odiv_diff <- Odiv_D[,1] - Odiv_N[,1] %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  select(Diversity=1)
Plot_D <- cbind(Odiv_diff, MH) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(x=MH,y=Diversity, col=Method)) +
  guides(col=guide_legend(title="Sample Type", override.aes=list(size=1)), size=F) +
  xlab("Morisita Horn") +
  ylab("Alpha Diversity -- Digested-Nondigested") +
  theme(text = element_text(size=15)) +
  ggthemes::scale_colour_wsj("colors6") +
  theme_bw()
Plot_D
